## 4. GitHub Actions (The Automation Engine)

These YAML files automate the workflow so the agent operates continuously without relying on your local machine.

### A. The Anchor (Syncs Notion to Repo)
**File:** `.github/workflows/01-sync-constitution.yml`

```yaml
name: 01 - Sync Notion Constitution
on:
  schedule:
    - cron: '0 0 * * *' # Runs every midnight UTC
  workflow_dispatch:    # Allows manual trigger

jobs:
  sync-truth:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: '20'
      - run: npm ci
      - name: Fetch Notion Requirements
        env:
          NOTION_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.NOTION_API_KEY }}
          NOTION_DB_ID: ${{ vars.NOTION_REQUIREMENTS_DB_ID }}
        run: npx tsx src/notion/sync-truth.ts
      - name: Commit Updated Cache
        run: |
          git config --global user.name 'github-actions[bot]'
          git config --global user.email 'github-actions[bot]@users.noreply.github.com'
          git add .truth-cache/
          git commit -m "chore: nightly Notion truth sync" || echo "No changes to commit"
          git push
```

### B. The Auditor (Scans Asana & Triggers Claude)
**File:** `.github/workflows/02-scan-frontier.yml`

```yaml
name: 02 - Scan Asana Frontier
on:
  schedule:
    - cron: '0 * * * *' # Runs every hour
  workflow_dispatch:

jobs:
  audit-asana:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v4
        with:
          node-version: '20'
      - run: npm ci
      - name: Install Claude CLI
        run: npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code
      - name: Run Truth Catcher Audit
        env:
          ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY }}
          ASANA_ACCESS_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.ASANA_ACCESS_TOKEN }}
          ASANA_PROJECT_GID: ${{ vars.ASANA_PROJECT_GID }}
        run: |
          claude --agent truth-catcher "Run an alignment audit on the recent Asana activity."
```

